# MONAI Deploy Workflow Manager Helm Repository

[![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/license-Apache%202.0-green.svg)](LICENSE)

## About

To install the workflow manager component of MONAI Deploy, a helm chart has been created for installing it into a Kubernetes Cluster.

The Workflow Manager has a secondary service called the Task Manager, which is responsible for executing each task within a workflow. By installing the `workflow-manager` helm chart, the `task-manager` chart will also be installed.

The MONAI Deploy Workflow Manager also has a number of 3rd party dependency charts, including:

 - monai-mongo (a slightly tweaked version of the MongoDB Community Operator)
 - RabbitMQ
 - MinIO

## Install Helm and add the monai-deploy repository

To get started, first install Helm. See their docs: https://helm.sh/docs/intro/install/

Secondly, add the MONAI Workflow Manager Helm repo as a repository to your helm:

```bash
$ helm repo add monai-deploy https://monai.io/monai-deploy-workflow-manager/
$ helm repo update
```

To see what versions are available for install, call the helm search command:

```bash
$ helm search repo monai-deploy
NAME                    CHART VERSION   APP VERSION     DESCRIPTION
monai/monai-mongodb     0.7.8           0.7.8           MongoDB Kubernetes Community Operator with MONA...
monai/task-manager      0.1.7           0.1.7           The MONAI Deploy Task Manager, responsible for ...
monai/workflow-manager  0.1.7           0.1.7           The Workflow Manager component of MONAI Deploy,...
```

## Install Workflow Manager (and its dependencies)

To install the MONAI Deploy Workflow Manager, first make sure your kubectl is connected to the correct Kubernetes context and then install the relevant chart:

```bash
$ helm upgrade -i -n monai --create-namespace workflow-manager monai-deploy/workflow-manager
```